Pupils and teachers of Life Frontier school on Friday made donations to a school for children living with disabilities in Garissa county. The pupils donate food and clothing to the Garissa Primary School for the physically handicapped and visually. It’sinformally known as the Mama Hani children’s home. Life Frontier School head teacher Eunice Muruiki said the visit was meant to teach their pupils the values of love and care. “We wanted to touch lives as we celebrated our 20-year anniversary.This activity today was meant to be a blessing to the children in this institution,” Muruiki said. She said that from next year such activities will be incorporated in the school’s calendar and will be done annually.